{"word":"θραύω","slug":"θραύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ϑραύω</el></b> [primitive word, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Lat.\">Lat.</a> frustum ‘bit, fragment’] <b>break</b> a jar of ointment <b><a href='B:480 14:3'>Mk 14:3</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a></b> —By <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ ext.\">ext.</a>, in imagery of the downtrodden or oppressed, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pass.\">pass.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ ptc.\">ptc.</a> <el>τεϑραυσμένος</el> broken/shattered (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> our ‘suffer a breakdown’) <b><a href='B:490 4:18'>Lk 4:18</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:θραυματίζω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:θρέμμα\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}